xdm:eventType.title: Event Type

meta:enum.leadOperation.statusInCampaignProgressio: Lead Operation Status In Campaign Progression Changed

xdm:eventMergeId.title: ExperienceEvent merge ID
xdm:eventMergeId.description: An ID to correlate or merge multiple Experience events together that are essentially the same event or should be merged. This is intended to be populated by the data producer prior to ingestion.

xdm:producedBy.title: Produced By
xdm:producedBy.description: Value that describes the producer of the event - suggested values would be 'self', 'system', 'salesRep', etc. Can be used to filter out certain producers if needed.

xdm:advertising.title: Advertising
xdm:advertising.description: Information related to advertising impressions, clickthroughs, and attribution.

xdm:adViewability.title: MRC viewability
xdm:adViewability.description: Media Rating Council (MRC) defines viewability as an online advertising metric that indicates the number of impressions that are actually “seen” by end-users. Viewability captures specific details such as player volume, library version, window status, and viewport ad measured dimensions.

xdm:adUnitDepth.title: Ad Unit Depth
xdm:adUnitDepth.description: Publishers may embed ad units inside containers/iFrames in order limit the ad's access solely to the code of the page. This describes how many 'containers' or iFrames the ad unit is displayed inside of.

xdm:viewportHeight.title: Viewport Height
xdm:viewportHeight.description: The vertical size (in pixels) of the window the experience was displayed inside measured at runtime. For a web view event, the browser viewport height.

xdm:viewportWidth.title: Viewport Width
xdm:viewportWidth.description: The horizontal size (in pixels) of the window the experience was displayed inside measured at runtime. For a web view event, the browser viewport width.

xdm:adHeight.title: Ad Height
xdm:adHeight.description: The number of vertical pixels of the player, measured at runtime. This can be larger than the size of the ad if the player has extra controls or thumbnails.

xdm:adWidth.title: Ad Width
xdm:adWidth.description: The number of horizontal pixels of the player, measured at runtime. This can be larger than the size of the ad if the player has extra controls or thumbnails.

xdm:playerVolume.title: Player Volume Percentage
xdm:playerVolume.description: The player volume percentage, measured at runtime where 0 is muted and 100 is maximum volume.

xdm:measurementEligible.title: Viewability Measurement Eligible
xdm:measurementEligible.description: Whether or not the ad was eligible to viewability measurement. An ad is eligible if the unit has a supported creative format and tag type.

xdm:implementationDetails.title: Viewabiltity Implementation Details
xdm:implementationDetails.description: The name and version of the library instrumented to measure viewability metrics.

xdm:name.title: Name
xdm:name.description: SDK or endpoint identifier. All SDKs or endpoints are identified through a URI, including extensions.

xdm:version.title: Version
xdm:version.description: The version identifier of the API, e.g h.18.

xdm:viewable.title: Viewable Ad
xdm:viewable.description: Display ads are considered viewable when at least 50% of the ad is visible for at least 1 second. Video ads are considered viewable when at least 50% of the ad is visible while the video is playing for at least 2 consecutive seconds. All viewable ads are measurable, because you can't confirm that an ad has met the criteria for viewability unless it can be measured.

xdm:activeWindow.title: Active Window
xdm:activeWindow.description: Indicates whether ad was shown on active window on users' device.

xdm:percentViewable.title: Percent Viewable
xdm:percentViewable.description: Percent of pixels in the ad deemed viewable at measurement time.

xdm:viewabilityEligibleImpressions.description: Impression(s) of an advertisement to an end-user with viewablility library instrumented.

xdm:id.title: Unique Identifier
xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:value.description: The quantifiable value of this measure.

xdm:measuredAdNotVisible.description: Indicator of ad not being visible as measured by a viewability library at impression time.

xdm:sessionLength.description: Length of the application session in seconds. Usually referred as the time the application was in foreground.

xdm:userPerspective.title: User Perspective
xdm:userPerspective.description: The perspective/physical relationship between the user and the app/brand at the time the event happened.  The most common are the app being in the foreground with the user directly interacting with it vs the app being in the background and still generating events.  Detached means the event was related to the app but didn't come directly from the app like the sending of an email or push notification from an external system.  Understanding the perspective of the user in relation to the app helps with accuratly generating sessions as the majority of the time you will not want to include background and detached events as part of an active session.

xdm:id.title: Unique Identifier
xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:thirdPartyCookiesEnabled.description: If third-party cookies were enabled when this observation was made.

xdm:viewportHeight.description: The vertical size in pixels of the window the experience was displayed inside. For a web view event, the browser viewport height.

xdm:viewportWidth.title: Viewport width
xdm:viewportWidth.description: The horizontal size in pixels of the window the experience was displayed inside. For a web view event, the browser viewport width.

xdm:userAgent.title: User agent
xdm:userAgent.description: The HTTP user-agent string from the client request.

items.description: User-agent associated commercial name with significant versions.

xdm:brand.description: The user-agent's commercial name (e.g., cURL, Edge).

xdm:version.description: The marketing version which includes distinguishable web-exposed features (e.g., 72, 3, or 12.1), corresponding to the user-agent.

xdm:mobile.description: A boolean indicating if the user agent's device is a mobile device.

xdm:architecture.description: The user agent's underlying CPU architecture (e.g., ARM, or x86).

xdm:bitness.title: Platform bitness
xdm:bitness.description: The user agent's underlying CPU architecture bitness (e.g., 32 or 64).

xdm:model.title: Model
xdm:model.description: The user agent's device model  (e.g., Pixel 2 XL).

xdm:platform.title: Platform
xdm:platform.description: The user agent's operating system's commercial name.

xdm:platformVersion.description: The user agent's operating system's version (e.g., NT 6.0, 15, or 17G).

xdm:wow64.title: WoW64-ness
xdm:wow64.description: A boolean indicating if the user agent's binary is running in 32-bit mode on 64-bit Windows.

xdm:operatingSystem.title: Operating system
xdm:operatingSystem.description: The name of the operating system used when the observation was made. The attribute should not contain any version information such as '10.5.3', but instead contain 'edition' designations such as 'Ultimate' or 'Professional'.

xdm:operatingSystemVersion.title: Operating system version
xdm:operatingSystemVersion.description: The full version identifier for the operating system used when the observation was made. Versions are generally numerically composed but may be in a vendor defined format.

xdm:operatingSystemVendor.title: Operating system vendor
xdm:operatingSystemVendor.description: The name of the operating system vendor used when the observation was made.

xdm:colorDepth.title: Color depth
xdm:colorDepth.description: The number of bits used for each color component of a single pixel.

xdm:viewportHeight.title: Viewport height
xdm:viewportHeight.description: The vertical size in pixels of the window the experience was displayed inside. For a web view event, the browser viewport height.

xdm:viewportWidth.title: Viewport width
xdm:viewportWidth.description: The horizontal size in pixels of the window the experience was displayed inside. For a web view event, the browser viewport width.

xdm:duration.title: Duration
xdm:duration.description: The number of milliseconds that the user was on the screen.

xdm:viewedScreen.title: Viewed Screen
xdm:viewedScreen.description: The friendly name assigned to the screen that the user was on.

xdm:previousScreen.title: Previous Screen
xdm:previousScreen.description: The frinedly name assigned to the screen the user was on prior to the viewedScreen.

xdm:carrier.title: Mobile network carrier
xdm:carrier.description: A mobile network carrier or MNO, also known as a wireless service provider, wireless carrier, cellular company, or mobile network carrier, is a provider of services wireless communications that owns or controls all the elements necessary to sell and deliver services to an end user.

xdm:domain.title: Domain
xdm:domain.description: The domain of the users ISP.

xdm:ISP.title: Internet service provider
xdm:ISP.description: The name of the user's internet service provider.

dc:language.title: Language
dc:language.description:
The language of the environment to represent the user's linguistic, geographical, or cultural preferences for data presentation.
Languages are specified in language code as defined in [IETF RFC 3066](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3066.txt), which is part of BCP 47, which is used elsewhere in XDM.

xdm:ipV4.title: IPv4
xdm:ipV4.description: The numerical label assigned to a device participating in a computer network that uses the Internet Protocol for communication.

xdm:ipV6.title: IPv6
xdm:ipV6.description: The numerical label assigned to a device participating in a computer network that uses the Internet Protocol for communication.

xdm:device.title: Device
xdm:device.description: An identified device, application or device browser instance that is trackable across sessions, normally by cookies.

xdm:typeID.title: Type identifier
xdm:typeID.description: An identifier for the device. This may be an identifier from 'DeviceAtlas' or another service that identifies the hardware that is being used.

xdm:typeIDService.title: Type identifier service
xdm:typeIDService.description: The namespace of the service that is used to identify the device type.

xdm:manufacturer.title: Manufacturer
xdm:manufacturer.description: The name of the organization who owns the design and creation of the device, for example, 'Apple' is the manufacturer of the iPhone.

xdm:model.title: Model
xdm:model.description: The name of the model for the device. This is the common, human-readable, or marketing name for the device. For example, the 'iPhone 6S' is a particular model of mobile phone.

xdm:modelNumber.title: Model number
xdm:modelNumber.description: The unique model number designation assigned by the manufacturer for this device. Model numbers are not versions, but unique identifiers that identify a particular model configuration. While the model for a particular phone might be 'iPhone 6S' the model number would be 'A1633', or 'A1634' based on configuration at the time of sale.

xdm:screenHeight.title: Screen height
xdm:screenHeight.description: The number of vertical pixels of the device's active display in the default orientation.

xdm:screenWidth.title: Screen width
xdm:screenWidth.description: The number of horizontal pixels of the device's active display in the default orientation.

xdm:colorDepth.title: Color depth
xdm:colorDepth.description: The number of colors the display is able to represent.

xdm:screenOrientation.title: Screen orientation
xdm:screenOrientation.description: The current screen orientation such as "portrait" or "landscape".

xdm:isBackgroundPushEnabled.title: Background Push Enabled Flag
xdm:isBackgroundPushEnabled.description: For devices like mobile , this tracks the system background push enabled permision status.

xdm:isLocationEnabled.title: Location Enabled Flag
xdm:isLocationEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not the device has location services enabled.

xdm:locationPermission.title: Location Permission
xdm:locationPermission.description: Tracks the device location permision attribute setting.

xdm:isPushOptIn.title: Push Opt In Flag
xdm:isPushOptIn.description: Indicates whether or not the device opted-in to receive push notifications.

xdm:placeContext.title: Place context
xdm:placeContext.description: The transient circumstances related to the observation. Examples include locale specific information such as weather, local time, traffic, day of the week, workday vs. holiday, and working hours.

xdm:localTime.title: Local time
xdm:localTime.description: The local time using RFC3339 with a stated time zone offset such as "2001-07-04T12:08:56-07:00". An example formatting pattern is "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssXXX".

xdm:ianaTimezone.title: Iana Timezone
xdm:ianaTimezone.description: Timezone of the device represented as a standard timezone string. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones.

xdm:localTimezoneOffset.title: Local time zone offset
xdm:localTimezoneOffset.description: The current, local time zone offset in minutes from UTC for the localTime in this object.  This will include the current DST offset if applicable.

xdm:stateProvince.description: The state, or province portion of the observation. The format follows the [ISO 3166-2 (country and subdivision)][http://www.unece.org/cefact/locode/subdivisions.html] standard.

xdm:postalCode.description: The postal code of the location. Postal codes are not available for all countries. In some countries, this will only contain part of the postal code.

In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:value.description: The quantifiable value of this measure.

xdm:pauses.title: Pause events
xdm:pauses.description: The number of pause periods that occurred during playback.

xdm:payload.title: Payload
xdm:payload.description: Values that are directly related with the segment realization. This payload exists with the same 'validUntil' as the segment realization. xdm:status.description: Is the segment participation realized as part of the current request.

meta:enum.existing: Entity continues to be in the segment.

xdm:tags.title: Tags
xdm:tags.description:
Tags are used to indicate how the aliases represented by a given data
source should be interpreted by applications using those aliases.

Examples:

* `isAVID`: data sources representing Analytics visitor IDs.
* `isCRSKey`: data sources representing aliases that should be used as keys in CRS.

Tags are set when the data source is created but they are also included in
pipeline messages when referencing a given data source.

xdm:siteSection.description: The normative name of the site section where this web page resides, which may be used to classify or categorize the interaction.

xdm:name.description: The normative name of the web page. This name is not necessarily the page title or directly associate with page content, but is used to organize a site's pages for classification purposes.

xdm:viewName.description: The name of the view, within a page. This is commonly used with Single Page Applications or pages that have tabs or controls that change a majority of the page layout.

xdm:URL.description: The normative or usual URL of the web page.  This may or may not be the actual URL used to reach the page, which would be recorded using `Web Link`.

xdm:server.description: The normative or usual server that hosts the web page.  This may or may not be the host or server that actually served the page interaction, but is used for classification purposes.

xdm:isErrorPage.description: Flag that indicate if the page is error page or not.  Error here is defined by the application, and may nor may not correspond to a page served with an HTTP error code.  This flag is used to broadly categorize web interactions.

xdm:isHomePage.description: Flag that indicate if the page is the site home page or not.  The definition of home page is determined by the application, but is commonly used to designate a top level landing page or common site entry point.  This flag is used to broadly categorize web interactions.

xdm:id.title: Unique Identifier
xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:productListItems.title: Product List Items
xdm:productListItems.description: A list of items representing a product selected by a customer with specific options and pricing that are for that usage context at a specific point of time and may differ from the product record.

xdm:SKU.title: SKU
xdm:SKU.description: Stock keeping unit (SKU), the unique identifier for a product defined by the vendor.

@id.title: Line item ID.
@id.description: The line item identifier for this product entry. The product itself is identified through `xdm:product`.

xdm:product.title: Product
xdm:product.description: The XDM identifier of the product itself.

xdm:name.title: Name
xdm:name.description: The display name for the product as presented to the user for this product view.

xdm:productAddMethod.title: Product add method
xdm:productAddMethod.description: The method that was used to add a product item to the list by the visitor. Set with product list add metrics.

xdm:currencyCode.title: Currency code
xdm:currencyCode.description: The ISO 4217 alphabetic currency code used for pricing the product.

xdm:quantity.title: Quantity
xdm:quantity.description: The number of units the customer has indicated they require of the product.

xdm:priceTotal.title: Price total
xdm:priceTotal.description: The total price for the product line item.

xdm:selectedOptions.title: Selected Options
xdm:selectedOptions.description: Particular options chosen for a configurable product.

items.title: Selected option
items.description: Selected option for one attribute of a configurable product

xdm:attribute.title: Configurable attribute name
xdm:attribute.description: The name of the configurable attribute

xdm:value.title: Selected option value
xdm:value.description: The value chosen for the configurable attribute

xdm:discountAmount.title: Discount Amount
xdm:discountAmount.description: The difference between the regular price and the special price for the product.

xdm:refundAmount.title: Refund Amount
xdm:refundAmount.description: Amount refunded for item, if any.

xdm:productCategories.title: Product categories
xdm:productCategories.description: List of category data this product falls under

xdm:unitOfMeasureCode.title: Product Unit Of Measure Code
xdm:unitOfMeasureCode.description: Standard unit of measure of the product and or variation and relates the units for the size measurement.

xdm:id.title: Unique Identifier
xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:commerce.title: Commerce
xdm:commerce.description: Product returns, warranty registration, and shopping cart/order process.

xdm:order.title: Order
xdm:order.description: The placed order for one or more products.

xdm:purchaseID.title: Purchase ID
xdm:purchaseID.description: Unique identifier assigned by the seller for this purchase or contract. There is no guarantee that the ID is unique.

xdm:purchaseOrderNumber.title: Purchase Order Number
xdm:purchaseOrderNumber.description: Unique identifier assigned by the purchaser for this purchase or contract.

xdm:payments.title: Payment List
xdm:payments.description: The list of payments for this order.

xdm:transactionID.title: Transaction ID
xdm:transactionID.description: The unique transaction identifier for this payment item.

xdm:paymentType.title: Payment Type
xdm:paymentType.description: The method of payment for this order. Enumerated, custom values allowed.

xdm:currencyCode.title: Currency Code
xdm:currencyCode.description: The ISO 4217 currency code used for this payment item.

xdm:refunds.title: Refunds List
xdm:refunds.description: The list of refunds for this order.

xdm:transactionID.title: Transaction ID
xdm:transactionID.description: The unique transaction identifier for this refund item.

xdm:refundReason.title: Refund Reason
xdm:refundReason.description: Reason why a refund was issued. Enumerated.

xdm:refundPaymentType.title: Refund Payment Type
xdm:refundPaymentType.description: The method of payment for this order. Enumerated, custom values allowed.

xdm:currencyCode.title: Currency Code
xdm:currencyCode.description: The ISO 4217 currency code used for this refund item.

xdm:currencyCode.title: Currency
xdm:currencyCode.description: The ISO 4217 currency code used for the order totals.

xdm:taxAmount.title: Tax Amount
xdm:taxAmount.description: The tax amount paid by the buyer as part of the final payment.

xdm:priceTotal.title: Price Total
xdm:priceTotal.description: The total price of this order after all discounts and taxes have been applied.

xdm:orderType.title: Order Type
xdm:orderType.description: The type order that has been placed.

xdm:lastUpdatedDate.title: Last Updated Date
xdm:lastUpdatedDate.description: The time when a particular order record is last updated in the commerce system.

xdm:createdDate.title: Created Date
xdm:createdDate.description: The time/date when a new order is created in the commerce system.

xdm:cancelDate.title: Cancel Date
xdm:cancelDate.description: The date/time when an order cancellation is initiated by the shopper.

xdm:promotionID.title: Promotion ID
xdm:promotionID.description: Promotion identifier if any for the order placed.

xdm:cartAbandons.title: Cart Abandons
xdm:cartAbandons.description: A product list has been identified as no longer accessible or purchasable by the user.

xdm:id.title: Unique Identifier
xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:shippingDestination.title: Shipping Destination
xdm:shippingDestination.description: The ship-to  destination specified by the user. It could be home, store etc.

xdm:shipDate.title: Ship Date
xdm:shipDate.description: The date when one or more items from an order is shipped.

@id.title: Coordinates ID
@id.description: The unique identifier of the coordinates.

schema:description.title: Description
schema:description.description: A description of what the coordinates identify.

schema:latitude.title: Latitude
schema:latitude.description: The signed vertical coordinate of a geographic point.

schema:longitude.title: Longitude
schema:longitude.description: The signed horizontal coordinate of a geographic point.

schema:elevation.title: Elevation
schema:elevation.description: The specific elevation of the defined coordinate. The value conforms to the [WGS84](http://gisgeography.com/wgs84-world-geodetic-system/) datum and is measured in meters.

xdm:countryCode.title: Country code
xdm:countryCode.description: The two-character [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2](https://datahub.io/core/country-list) code for the country.

xdm:stateProvince.title: State or province
xdm:stateProvince.description: The state, or province portion of the observation. The format follows the [ISO 3166-2 (country and subdivision)][http://www.unece.org/cefact/locode/subdivisions.html] standard.

xdm:postalCode.title: Postal code
xdm:postalCode.description: The postal code of the location. Postal codes are not available for all countries. In some countries, this will only contain part of the postal code.

xdm:dmaID.title: Designated market area
xdm:dmaID.description: The Nielsen media research designated market area.

xdm:msaID.title: Metropolitan statistical area
xdm:msaID.description: The metropolitan statistical area in the United States where the observation occurred.

xdm:repositoryCreatedBy.title: Created by user identifier
xdm:repositoryCreatedBy.description: User ID of who created the record.

xdm:repositoryLastModifiedBy.title: Modified by user identifier
xdm:repositoryLastModifiedBy.description: User ID of who last modified the record. At creation time, `modifiedByUser` is set as `createdByUser`.

xdm:createdByBatchID.title: Created by batch identifier
xdm:createdByBatchID.description: The dataset files in Catalog which has been originating the creation of the record.

xdm:modifiedByBatchID.title: Modified by batch identifier
xdm:modifiedByBatchID.description: The last dataset files in Catalog which has modified the record. At creation time, `modifiedByBatchID` is set as `createdByBatchID`.

repo:createDate.description: The server date and time when the resource was created in the repository, such as when an asset file is first uploaded or a directory is created by the server as the parent of a new asset. The date time property should conform to ISO 8601 standard. An example form is "2004-10-23T12:00:00-06:00".

repo:modifyDate.description: The server date and time when the resource was last modified in the repository, such as when a new version of an asset is uploaded or a directory's child resource is added or removed. The date time property should conform to ISO 8601 standard. An example form is "2004-10-23T12:00:00-06:00".

xdm:primary.title: Primary
xdm:primary.description: Primary address indicator. A profile can have only one `primary` address at a given point of time.

xdm:label.title: Label
xdm:label.description: Free form name of the address.

xdm:street1.title: Street 1
xdm:street1.description: Primary street level information, apartment number, street number, and street name.

xdm:region.title: Region
xdm:region.description: The region, county, or district portion of the address.

xdm:postOfficeBox.title: Post office box
xdm:postOfficeBox.description: Post office box of the address.

xdm:country.title: Country
xdm:country.description: The name of the government-administered territory. Other than `xdm:countryCode`, this is a free-form field that can have the country name in any language.

xdm:state.title: State
xdm:state.description: The name of the State. This is a free-form field.

xdm:status.title: Status
xdm:status.description: An indication as to the ability to use the address.

xdm:statusReason.title: Status reason
xdm:statusReason.description: A description of the current status.

xdm:lastVerifiedDate.title: Last verified date
xdm:lastVerifiedDate.description: The date that the address was last verified as still associated to the person.

xdm:trackingNumber.title: Tracking Number
xdm:trackingNumber.description: The tracking number provided by the shipping carrier for a order item shipment.

xdm:trackingURL.title: Tracking URL
xdm:trackingURL.description: The URL to track the shipping status of an order item.

xdm:instantPurchase.description: A product has been purchased instantly, potentially skipping the cart or checkout.

xdm:id.title: Unique Identifier
xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:value.description: The quantifiable value of this measure.

xdm:requisitionListOpens.title: Requisition List Opens
xdm:requisitionListOpens.description: Initializations of a new Requisition List.

xdm:requisitionListAdds.description: Addition of a product(s) to a requisition list.

xdm:requisitionListRemovals.description: Removal of a product(s) from a requisition product list.

xdm:requisitionList.title: Requisition List
xdm:requisitionList.description: The properties of requisition list created by customer.

xdm:ID.title: Requisition List ID
xdm:ID.description: Unique identifier of the requisition list.

xdm:name.title: Requisition List Name
xdm:name.description: Name of the requisition list specified by the customer.

xdm:description.title: Requisition List Description
xdm:description.description: Description of the requisition list specified by the customer.

https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decision.title: Proposition Event
https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decision.description: A record of how the user interacted with the proposition. All propositions recorded on this event will be associated with the same event that is recorded here.

xdm:send.title: send
xdm:send.description: Proposition was sent to the client. This does not guarantee the proposition arrived or was displayed to the user.

xdm:trigger.title: trigger
xdm:trigger.description: Proposition was chosen to be displayed by the client SDK. Other factors may prevent it from actually being displayed.

xdm:display.title: display
xdm:display.description: Proposition was displayed to the user.

xdm:interact.title: interact
xdm:interact.description: User interacted with the proposition, usually in a positive way.

xdm:dismiss.title: dismiss
xdm:dismiss.description: User dismissed or rejected the proposition without any other direct interaction.

xdm:unsubscribe.title: unsubscribe
xdm:unsubscribe.description: User has requested to not be shown the proposition in the future.

https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decision.title: Proposition Action
https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decision.description: The specific element that was interacted with which caused the proposition event to be triggered.

xdm:id.title: id
xdm:id.description: The customer generated id of the element with which the end-user interacted.

xdm:label.title: label
xdm:label.description: The customer generated display name of the element with which the end-user interacted.

https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decision.title: Involved Propositions
https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decision.description: An array of decision propositions that contributed to the experience event. The experience event is attributed (at least partially) to those prior decisions/propositions. An individual profile's proposition-response history is maintained with these decision identifiers.

xdm:id.title: Decision Proposition Identifier
xdm:id.description: The unique identifier of the proposition that originally contained the decision options that are being acted upon (see the corresponding 'items' field in this object). When this identifier is present, direct attribution is given to a unique proposition. If the identifier is missing, the action for the items could not be assiciated with a unique proposition.

xdm:scope.title: Decision Scope
xdm:scope.description: The scope that is associated with the decision. This is the name of the scope that was in the request when the decision was made.

xdm:items.title: Selected Options
xdm:items.description: One or more of the previously proposed options that this experience event is related to. Those items were returned as output of the decision for a requested scope and are now part of an interaction. For instance, if the decision returned five proposed videos to watch and the user selected two in a "Save For Later" interaction, then this experience event could record the user's reaction with an event type "custom.savedToWatchLater" and list the two selected videos in the 'items' array.

items.description: An item from the proposition's options. See 'selections' of the 'Decision Proposition Detail' mix-in.

xdm:id.title: Decision Option Identifier
xdm:id.description: A unique identifier for the decision option.

repo:etag.title: Decision Option ETag
repo:etag.description: The revision that the decision option object was at when the snapshot was taken.

xdm:name.title: Decision Option Name
xdm:name.description: Option name. The name is displayed in various user interfaces.

xdm:tags.title: Decision Option Tags
xdm:tags.description: The set of tags associated with this option. The tags are used indicate catetoegies (dimensions) that the option belonged to at the time the proposition was made.

items.description: An identifier of a Tag object. The value is the @id of the Tag that is referenced. See Tag schema https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decisioning/tag

xdm:characteristics.title: Decision Option Characteristics
xdm:characteristics.description: Additional properties or attributes belonging to this particular decision option. Different instances can have different characteristics (keys in the map). The characteristics are name value pairs used to distinguish one decision option from others. Characteristics are used as values in content that represents this decision option and as features to analyze and optimize the performance of an option. When every instance has the same attribute or property, that aspect should be modeled as an extension schema that derives from decision option detail.

xdm:score.title: Decision Option Score
xdm:score.description: Calcuated value for that option in the context of a single scope. The value is only available if a score was calculated.

xdm:optionContent.title: Option Content
xdm:optionContent.description: Additional properties or attributes related to offer content

@type.description: Content Component Type. An enumerated set of URIs where each value maps to a type given to the content component. Some consumers of the content representations are expecting the @type value to be a reference to schema that describes additional properties of the content component.
@type.title: Content Component Type

dc:format.title: Format
dc:format.description: The physical or digital manifestation of the resource. Typically, Format should include the media-type of the resource. Format may be used to determine the software, hardware or other equipment needed to display or operate the resource. Recommended best practice is to select a value from a controlled vocabulary (for example, the list of [Internet Media Types](http://www.iana.org/ assignments/media-types/) defining computer media formats).

dc:language.title: Language
dc:language.description:
The language or languages of the resource.
Languages are specified in language code as defined in [IETF RFC 3066](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3066.txt), which is part of BCP 47, which is used elsewhere in XDM.

repo:name.description: Some hint about where to locate the repository that stores the external asset by the "repo:id".

repo:repositoryID.description: An optional unique identifier to reference the asset in a content repository. When Platform APIs are used to retrieve the representation the client can expect an addtional propery "repo:resolveUrl" to retrieve the asset.

repo:id.description: An optional unique identifier to reference the asset in a content repository. When Platform APIs are used to retrieve the representation the client can expect an addtional propery "repo:resolveUrl" to retrieve the asset.

repo:resolveURL.description: An optional unique resource locator to read the asset in a content repository. This will make it easier to obtain the asset whithout the client understanding where the asset is manages and what APIs to call. This is similar to a HAL link but the semantic is simpler and more pursposeful.

xdm:content.description: An optional field to hold content directly. Instead of referencing content in an asset repository the component can hold simple content directly. This field is not used for composite, complex and binary content assets.

xdm:deliveryURL.description: An optional unique resource locator to obtain the asset from a content delivery network or service endpoint. This URL is used to access the asset publicly by a user agent.

xdm:linkURL.description: An optional unique resource locator for user interactions. This URL is used to refer the end user to in a user agent and can be tracked.

https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decision.description: The total number a particular option was proposed so far across all profiles.

xdm:id.title: Unique Identifier
xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:value.description: The quantifiable value of this measure.

https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decision.description: The number of times a particular option was proposed so far to a particular profile. When this metric is present the record or time-series entity must include an IdentityMap the profile.

xdm:id.title: Unique Identifier
xdm:id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

xdm:value.description: The quantifiable value of this measure.

xdm:scopeDetails.title: Decision Scope Snapshot
xdm:scopeDetails.description: A snapshot of properties from the decision scope. This is the state of the scope entity that was used in the decision requst.

xdm:id.title: Decision Scope Identifier
xdm:id.description: The unique identifier of the decision scope. For a given decision request a scope narrows the decision process along multiple dimensions. The scope is referencable by its identifier.

xdm:decisionProvider.title: Decision Provider
xdm:decisionProvider.description: The provider that was asked to make the decision. This dimension is used when mutliple services can make decisions for the same placement or activity.

xdm:placement.title: Placement Detail for the Scope
xdm:placement.description: The placement that was a requested as part of this decision scope. A scope will include a specification of the location or surface where the option will be presented. The placement narrows the options that can be proposed to those that can be represented or rendered in that place.

xdm:id.title: Placement Identifier
xdm:id.description: A unique identifier for the decision placement.

repo:etag.title: Placement ETag
repo:etag.description: The revision that the placement object was at when the snapshot was taken.

xdm:name.title: Placement Name
xdm:name.description: Placement name. The name is displayed in various user interfaces.

xdm:channelID.title: Placement's Channel Identifier
xdm:channelID.description: The channel in which proposition was made. The value is a valid Channel URI. See 'https://ns.adobe.com/xdm/channels/channel'

xdm:activity.title: Activity Detail for the Scope
xdm:activity.description: The activity that was a requested or chosen for this decision scope. Some scopes will prescribe the exact activity (why and how) that makes the decision, other scopes will use a dynamic strategy determine which activity is used. Those scopes will list executionDetails for steps that were performed during decision-making.

xdm:id.title: Activity Identifier
xdm:id.description: A unique, immutable identifier for the decision activity.

repo:etag.title: Activity ETag
repo:etag.description: The revision that the decision activity object was at when the snapshot was taken.

xdm:name.title: Activity Name
xdm:name.description: Activity name. The name is displayed in various user interfaces.

xdm:startTime.title: Activity Start Date and Time
xdm:startTime.description: Activity start date and end time. Property has the semantic of schema.org's 'startTime' property defined on http://schema.org/Action

xdm:endTime.title: Activity End Date and Time
xdm:endTime.description: Activity end date and end time. Property has the semantic of schema.org's 'endTime' property defined on http://schema.org/Action

xdm:fallback.title: Fallback Option
xdm:fallback.description: The reference to a fallback option that is used when decisioning in the context of this activity does not qualify any of the regular options (this typically happens when hard constraints are applied). The value is the URI (@id) of the fallback option that is referenced.

xdm:correlationID.title: Correlation Identifier
xdm:correlationID.description: The campaign, journey, or other object to which this activity can be correlated. This string will often be further classified in the reporting engine.

xdm:observation.title: Event observation
xdm:observation.description: A qualification that is evaluated against the experience event to test if a measurable outcome has been achieved. This mapping could check if the value of a property matches a given constant or could be a more complex evaluation. An outcome will be recorded with the event if and only if the implied condition evaluates to 'true'

xdm:mapping.title: Mapping type
xdm:mapping.description: Indicator for how the observation is mapped into an outcome value

xdm:value.title: Observation mapping
xdm:value.description: The expression or term that defines how the outcome is derived from the observation. The presence and interpretation of this 'value' is based on the 'mapping' type

xdm:field.title: Field name
xdm:field.description: The field that contains the observed value.

@id.title: Outcome identifier
@id.description: Unique value that identifies the outcome of the interaction (nominal value).

xdm:field.title: Outcome property path
xdm:field.description: Property path where the outcome is inserted into the XDM event.

xdm:outcome.title: Interaction outcome measurement
xdm:outcome.description: The definition of a measurement for the outcome. A property path and value is specified where a measured outcome for the interaction is recorded.

xdm:interactionMeasurements.title: Interaction Measurements used in this Scope
xdm:interactionMeasurements.description: The interaction measurements determine how inteaction event properties are interpreted (mapped) into outcomes for the propositions. Outcomes could be measured as the number of successes or failures or by a quantitative metric. An outcome can have a nominal value (e.g. success/failure), ordinal (rating value gathered) or numerical value (e.g. a measurable quantity).

xdm:step.title: Execution Step
xdm:step.description: Indicator for the step type in the overall decision strategy

xdm:strategyID.title: Step's Strategy Identifier
xdm:strategyID.description: The unique identifier of the step's strategy. When executing a decision various steps are performed. Each step is performed according to a strategy or policy and the chosen idetifier is recorded to measure its performance. This identifier could be the URI of a profile merge policy, an eligibility rule, a ML ranking strategy, a function that calculates the rank, a capping threshold or any object that signficantly contributes to the decision result.

xdm:algorithmID.title: Algorithm Identifier
xdm:algorithmID.description: Unique identifier for the algorithm used to make the decision, if applicable.

xdm:treatmentID.title: Treatment Identifier
xdm:treatmentID.description: Identifier for the experiment treatment or traffic allocation strategy that was selected for the decision.

xdm:trafficType.title: Traffic Type
xdm:trafficType.description: The class of algorithm/policy that was used to compute this decision. 'Contextual Traffic' indicates that event and profile context were used in deciding what to show. Noncontextual means that the decision was not made based on any contextual data. Random indicates that the decision was made by some pseudo-random process.

xdm:strategies.title: Strategy Step Details
xdm:strategies.description: The steps that were executed when the decision was made.

xdm:experience.title: Selected Experience Option
xdm:experience.description: The experience that was selected when the decision was made.

xdm:id.title: Experience Identifier
xdm:id.description: A unique identifier for the decision option.

xdm:characteristics.title: Scope Details Characteristics
xdm:characteristics.description: Additional properties or attributes belonging to this particular scope details.

xdm:decisionEventID.title: Decision Event Identifier (deprecated)
xdm:decisionEventID.description: The unique identifier of the decision event that proposed the 'items' (options). For a given decision request and profile identity the output of the decision is a unique event. If a decision is requested again for the same profile and the output are the same options, it is still considered a different proposition with a unique event ID. Multiple propositions can be associated with the same decision event. See https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decisioning/proposition. (deprecated)

xdm:decisionEventDetails.title: Decision Event Details (deprecated)
xdm:decisionEventDetails.description: A snapshot of properties from the decision event when it occured. (deprecated)

xdm:experienceID.title: Experience Reference
xdm:experienceID.description: Unique identifier for the proposition's content. Recipients of propositions with the same value will receive the same content experience in the targeted placements. Moreover, propositions with the same value to the same user mean that the content of the propositions has not changed. Propositions with values indicate that the decision selections are different and a different experience resulted from the decision. Note that adding a placement to the decision scope always changes the experience value.

xdm:algorithmID.title: Algorithm Reference
xdm:algorithmID.description: Unique identifier for the algorithm used to make the decision, if applicable.

xdm:trafficType.title: Traffic Type
xdm:trafficType.description: The class of algorithm/policy that was used to serve this decision. Contextual indicates that event and profile context were used in deciding what to show. Noncontextual means that the decision was not made based on any contextual data. Random indicates that the decision was made by some pseudo-random process.

xdm:decisionScope.title: Decision Event Scope (deprecated)
xdm:decisionScope.description: The scope that is associated with the decision. This is the name of the scope that was in the request when the decision was made. See https://ns.adobe.com/experience/decisioning/scope-details.(deprecated)

xdm:decisionScopeDetails.title: Decision Event Scope Details (deprecated)
xdm:decisionScopeDetails.description: A snapshot of properties from the decision scope. This is the state of the scope entity that was used in the decision requst. (deprecated)

xdm:id.title: Decision Scope Identifier
xdm:id.description: The unique identifier of the decision scope. For a given decision request a scope narrows the decision process along multiple dimensions. The scope is referencable by its identifier.

xdm:decisionProvider.title: Decision Provider
xdm:decisionProvider.description: The provider that was asked to make the decision. This dimension is used when mutliple services can make decisions for the same placement or activity.

xdm:id.description: A unique identifier for the decision placement.

xdm:name.title: Placement Name
xdm:name.description: Placement name. The name is displayed in various user interfaces.

xdm:channelID.title: Placement's Channel Identifier
xdm:channelID.description: The channel in which proposition was made. The value is a valid Channel URI. See 'https://ns.adobe.com/xdm/channels/channel'

xdm:name.title: Activity Name

xdm:endTime.title: Activity End Date and Time
xdm:endTime.description: Activity end date and end time. Property has the semantic of schema.org's 'endTime' property defined on http://schema.org/Action

This identifier could be the URI of a profile merge policy, an eligibility rule, a ML ranking strategy, a function that calculates the rank, a capping threshold or any object that signficantly contributes to the decision result.

xdm:algorithmID.title: Algorithm Identifier
xdm:algorithmID.description: Unique identifier for the algorithm used to make the decision, if applicable.

xdm:treatmentID.title: Treatment Identifier
xdm:treatmentID.description: Identifier for the experiment treatment or traffic allocation strategy that was selected for the decision.

xdm:trafficType.title: Traffic Type
xdm:trafficType.description: The class of algorithm/policy that was used to compute this decision. 'Contextual Traffic' indicates that event and profile context were used in deciding what to show. Noncontextual means that the decision was not made based on any contextual data. Random indicates that the decision was made by some pseudo-random process.

xdm:strategies.title: Strategy Step Details
xdm:strategies.description: The steps that were executed when the decision was made.

xdm:experience.title: Selected Experience Option
xdm:experience.description: The experience that was selected when the decision was made.

xdm:id.title: Experience Identifier
xdm:id.description: A unique identifier for the decision option.

xdm:characteristics.title: Scope Details Characteristics
xdm:characteristics.description: Additional properties or attributes belonging to this particular scope details.
